### Our Strategic Approach

**Differentiation:** While competitors present whimsigoth nails as a visual gallery, Mirellé will be the first to help readers understand the aesthetic's logic — what makes a set feel truly whimsigoth, where it sits relative to adjacent aesthetics, and how to build a cohesive set that feels intentional rather than assembled. The cultural reference mapping (Practical Magic, Stevie Nicks, Tim Burton) gives readers emotional anchor points that make the inspo feel personal, not just pretty.

**Structure plan:** Open with aesthetic definition and cultural anchors, then move through design elements (colour, motifs, texture, shape) in a way that builds understanding progressively. End with how the aesthetic behaves year-round, not just seasonally.

